      "source": [
        "# ARIMA & GARCH | US Treasury Yield Curve\n",
        "### Box-Jenkins Methodology | Econometrics II\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "**Series:** 10Y (`DGS10`) and 2Y (`DGS2`) Treasury yields from FRED  \n",
        "**Goal:** Model and forecast yield dynamics using the full Box-Jenkins pipeline + GARCH volatility\n",
        "\n",
        "The yield curve is Treasury yields plotted across maturities. The 10Y–2Y spread is inverted before every US recession since 1955.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "### Structure\n",
        "```\n",
        "0 │ Config — change series/dates/horizon here, everything else updates\n",
        "1 │ Data loading & visualisation\n",
        "2 │ Stationarity — ADF + KPSS, d selected automatically\n",
        "3 │ Box-Jenkins identification — ACF / PACF\n",
        "4 │ ARIMA estimation — grid search + diagnostics\n",
        "5 │ GARCH(1,1) — volatility modelling\n",
        "6 │ Forecasting — yield path + vol, GARCH-adjusted confidence bands\n",
        "7 │ Summary\n",
        "```"
      ]
    },
