        "## Part 5 | GARCH(1,1)\n",
        "\n",
        "GARCH(1,1) variance equation:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\sigma^2_t = \\omega + \\alpha \\varepsilon^2_{t-1} + \\beta \\sigma^2_{t-1}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "- ω = baseline variance\n",
        "- α = how much yesterday's shock feeds into today's variance\n",
        "- β = how persistent that variance is\n",
        "- α + β must be < 1 for stationarity; for financial series it's usually ~0.98–0.99\n",
        "\n",
        "VaR calculations, Basel III capital models, and options pricing"
      ]
